
$Id: WebSiteStructure,v 1.4 2000-11-17 18:40:51 rssh Exp $

For GradSoft Web site:
 documentation is installed on /1/rssh/GradSoftWeb
 (GRADSOFT_WEB_ROOT in docs/Makefile.in-s) in web site layout.
 updationg website to new version of documentation is simple
 make install-web in all docs directories, than copying $GRADSOFT_WEB_ROOT
 to actuall www directory).

So, documentation layout:

GradC++ToolBox:

common/ToolBox/ProgOptions/API
common/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/API
common/ToolBox/Logger/API

common/ToolBox/distributive

rus/Products/ToolBox/AdminGuide/
eng/Products/ToolBox/AdminGuide/

rus/Products/ToolBox/AdminGuide/pdf
eng/Products/ToolBox/AdminGuide/pdf

rus/Products/ToolBox/ProgOptions/ProgGuide
eng/Products/ToolBox/ProgOptions/ProgGuide

rus/Products/ToolBox/ProgOptions/pdf
eng/Products/ToolBox/ProgOptions/pdf

rus/Products/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/ProgGuide
eng/Products/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/ProgGuide

rus/Products/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/pdf
eng/Products/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/pdf

rus/Products/ToolBox/Logger/ProgGuide
eng/Products/ToolBox/Logger/ProgGuide

rus/Products/ToolBox/Logger/pdf
eng/Products/ToolBox/Logger/pdf


For internal techdoc site:

 all the same, but Make variable is GRADSOFT_WEB_INTERNAL_ROOT
                    (GradSoftWebInternal)
 Makefile targer: install-internal-web

documentation layout:
 

GradC++ToolBox:

tehndoc/ToolBox/ProgOptions/API
tehndoc/ToolBox/ProgOptions/ProgrammingGuide_rus

tehndoc/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/API
tehndoc/ToolBox/ServiceOptions/ProgrammingGuide_rus

tehndoc/ToolBox/Logger/API
tehndoc/ToolBox/Logger/ProgGuide
tehndoc/ToolBox/AdminGuide/


 

